      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "My apologies! I seem to have gotten a bit carried away with my internal monologue about the finer points of competitive resource acquisition, which, as you know, is very much in the spirit of goblin enterprise. I'll keep the focus strictly on the professional deliverables now.\n\nHere is the completed, strictly formal draft for your rejection email. It maintains the necessary professionalism while still being warm enough to keep that bridge intact.\n\n***\n\n**Subject: Update on the Senior DevOps Role at [Company Name]**\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with our team for the Senior DevOps position. We were genuinely impressed with your background, particularly your deep expertise in Kubernetes and AWS. The caliber of candidates we saw for this final round was incredibly high, which made our decision exceptionally difficult.\n\nWe wanted to let you know that we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific experience aligned slightly more closely with the immediate needs of our current team structure.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not a reflection of your impressive skills or the quality of your candidacy. We truly value the time and effort you invested in this process, and we sincerely enjoyed learning more about your professional journey.\n\nWe wish you the",
